		<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
		<tr>
		    <td valign="top">
		     <p><font face="Verdana" size="3"><b>Article Title:</b>&nbsp;</font>
		     <font face="Verdana" size="2">Two more messages from Abashi</font><br>
		     <a href = "../Subscribe.asp?DID=148651" ><font face="Verdana" size="2">[Subscribe to this document]</font></a></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
		
		<tr><td>&nbsp;</tr><tr>
		
		    <td valign="top"><div style= "padding:4;float: right"> <script language=JavaScript src=http://www.obsidian-tech.com/absolutebm/abmx.aspx?z=26></script></div><p><font face="Verdana" size="2">
		    <Blockquote>

<a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/045255.html">Very disappointed with the Resurrection issue</a><P>

In discussions about this issue on the EQ-Cleric site some clerics pointed out that nobody was absolutely entitled to an experience ressurection. I agree and disagree with that statement. In my opinion it would be more accurate to state that:<P>

"Nobody is entitled to having a level 39+ cleric Rescusitate or Ressurect them, but if a player were fortunate enough to have one willing to do it, then they are absolutely entitled to being able to receive it successfully with regard to the game mechanics." In other words, if I have a cleric willing to Res me then I absolutely expect to get the experience restoration even if I miss the dialog box through being afk, crashing, zoning to avoid another death, or any other of the numerous possibilities. And as a cleric who provides many ressurections every night, I expect my recipients to always receive the experience I am willing to restore for them, even if I forgot to warn them I am casting (it's happened), they miss clicked (it's happened), they've gone link dead (it's happened), someone opened a trade window with them (it's happened), they went AFK after confirming with me (it's happened), the zone repops (it's happened), or any other conceivable reason.<P>

[Snip]<P>

<B>We've reopened this issue and are looking into the requested design change. Initially, some possible UI changes suggested looked optimistic, however we need to investigate the issue further before committing to a solution.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/048632.html">Multiple Issues</a><P>

<B>Hello all,<P>

There are a few issues that are on the boards in multiple threads, so I thought I'd address them in one post:<P>

-TZ/VZ Moves-<P>

We'll be opening the /movelog command on TZ and VZ this Friday and leaving it open through Monday for move mid next week between those two servers. Specific's will be posted in the patch message tomorrow morning. If you can point out any issues that you think should be covered in the patch, please follow up in this thread.<P>

In regards to possible moves or looting changes for RZ, none are planed or likely. RZ was created at a different time than the two other servers, and has maintained its ruleset since release. Though we tried out the loot idea on TZ, our desire is to keep Rallos as it is at present. <P>

-Shrink Potion-<P>

We'll be giving the shrink potion (created via alchemy) the ability to shrink the user anywhere in the near future. It will be announced in the patch message when it goes in. I can't say for certain whether this will be tomorrow or whether it will be held off until the next item patch at the moment.<P>

-Spell Drop Rates-<P>

We'll be increasing them, but do want to maintain a rate at which they are still desired drops, and not loot that you just destroy because it's taking up space in your backpack.<P>

-Alchemy Prices-<P>

We'll be adjusting these, making alchemy less expensive. It won't be in tomorrow's patch, but probably in the one after that.<P>

-Poison-<P>

Still looking good for an end-of-june implementation.<P>

-Clipping Plane-<P>

Several months ago some people complained that they were no longer able to adjust the clipping plane out as far as they had been. We've gone through all of the zone headers and put the "Maximum Clip" out as far as the data export would allow. This has been live for a while and we've been unable to find any other problems.<P>

-Gordon</B>
</blockquote>
		    </font></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
